%h1 Category Management
.pull-right
  = link_to new_category_path, class: 'btn btn-default modal-link' do
    %i.fa.fa-pencil
    &nbsp;
    New Category
.pull-left
  %p Create categories to organize your pages and posts, and make navigation a snap. DToR makes it simple - just edit 'n go.
  %br
  #flashed-alert.text-primary= notice
- if @categories.empty?
  .row
    .col-xs-12
      %blockquote.text-primary Um, well, we don't know how to tell you this. But this is kinda sorta empty. You're gonna have to fill it with content to make it look nice and pretty... Smiles!
- else
  %table.table.table-striped.table-responsive
    %thead
      %tr
        %th Name
        %th{colspan: '3'}
    %tbody
      - @categories.each do |category|
        %tr
          %td= link_to category.name, category_posts_path(category), class: 'btn btn-sm btn-link'
          %td{width: 40}= link_to 'Details', category, class: 'btn btn-sm btn-primary modal-link'
          %td{width: 40}= link_to 'Manage', edit_category_path(category), class: 'btn btn-sm btn-warning modal-link'
          %td{width: 40}= link_to 'Delete', category, method: :delete, data: { confirm: 'Are you sure?' }, class: 'btn btn-sm btn-danger'
  %br